    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In the 18th and 19th centuries Dover housed iron works, machine shops, and a large hosiery factory owned by MacGregors.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dover%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Baker’s Opera House on Blackwell Street, a National Register landmark, once hosted touring Broadway productions.",
